  - question: "What is the difference between a UV nail lamp and an LED nail lamp?"
    answer: "Both cure gel polish using UV wavelengths — the difference is the bulb type and spectrum. Traditional UV lamps use fluorescent tubes emitting a broad 300–410nm spectrum; LED lamps use diodes emitting a narrower, targeted range (typically 365–405nm). LED cures in 30–60 seconds vs 2–4 minutes for old-style UV tubes. All modern MelodySusie lamps are dual UV/LED, meaning they cover both wavelengths and work with every gel formula on the market."

  - question: "Can a UV/LED nail lamp cure all gel polishes?"
    answer: "A dual UV/LED lamp cures virtually all modern gel polishes, builder gels, poly gels, and rhinestone adhesives. Old-formula gels designed specifically for fluorescent UV tubes may need longer cure times. MelodySusie's lamps emit both 365nm and 405nm wavelengths, which covers both UV-only and LED-optimized formulas — so compatibility is essentially universal."

  - question: "How many watts do I need for a nail lamp at home?"
