  - question: "Is LED or UV safer for your skin during gel manicures?"
    answer: "LED lamps expose your skin to UV rays for less time because they cure faster — that's the main safety advantage. Both lamp types emit UVA light, which is the same wavelength that causes tanning. Dermatologists recommend applying sunscreen on your hands before curing if you do gel nails frequently. For the highest skin protection available, the MelodySusie P-Plus20F has physical UV-blocking zoned light technology that directs light onto nails while minimizing exposure to surrounding skin."

