  - question: "What does low-heat mode do on a nail lamp?"
    answer: "Low-heat mode (typically the 99s setting on MelodySusie lamps) starts the lamp at reduced intensity and gradually increases power. This prevents the heat spike that makes some people pull their hand out mid-cure. It is especially useful for builder gel, thick color gels, and anyone with thin or sensitive nails. The P-PLUS30G includes this feature; it is the mode to use when curing gel feels uncomfortable."

  - question: "Can I use a cordless nail lamp at the salon?"
